From be3ecca91d69c28b1891800d0b8f0ada10255a41 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: korchasa <korchasa@icloud.com>
Date: Thu, 11 Jun 2026 20:57:52 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(engine): add runs doctor journal health checker with
 mechanical repair (FR-E83)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add `flowai-workflow runs doctor --workflow <dir> --run <runId>` that
diagnoses a run's durability artifacts and applies ONLY safe mechanical
repairs.

Checks (reporting every problem, grouped by severity; exit 0 iff no ERROR):
- journal integrity: line-level lint — torn final line = WARNING; non-final
  unparsable / unknown kind / non-monotonic seq = ERROR; duplicate event_id
  = WARNING.
- replay invariants: reuses the EXISTING replayer (run-journal.ts) as the
  single source of replay truth — events-after-terminal, undeclared-node
  lifecycle, attempt_completed without attempt_started, and per-node cost
  reconciliation.
- filesystem cross-check: orphan node dirs, missing declared dirs, stale
  runs/.lock (WARNING).

--repair drops a torn final line (backup journal.jsonl.bak, write-tmp +
atomic rename) and removes a stale lock; refuses (nothing modified) on a
live lock or journal/replay errors beyond a torn tail. --json emits a
machine-readable findings list.

Reuses getRunDir/getJournalPath and defaultLockPath/readLockInfo; exports
lock.ts::isLockHeldByLiveProcess for the liveness probe (no duplication).
Registers FR-E83 in the engine SRS + index + SDS.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
