+### 3.83 FR-E83: Run Doctor — Journal Health Check & Mechanical Repair
+
+- **Description:** A `runs doctor --workflow <dir> --run <runId>` CLI
+  subcommand diagnoses a run's durability artifacts and can apply ONLY safe
+  mechanical repairs. It reports EVERY problem found (not just the first),
+  grouped by severity (ERROR / WARNING / OK summary), and exits 0 when no
+  ERRORs, 1 otherwise.
+
+  **Checks (in order):**
+  1. *Journal integrity* — `journal.jsonl` exists; every line parses as JSON;
+     a truncated/garbage FINAL line is a WARNING (the writer already tolerates
+     it), a non-final unparsable line is an ERROR; unknown event `kind` is an
+     ERROR; non-monotonic `seq` is an ERROR; duplicate `event_id` is a WARNING
+     (the replayer dedupes).
+  2. *Replay invariants* — replay via the EXISTING replayer
+     (`run-journal.ts::replayRunJournal`; writing a second replayer is
+     forbidden — doctor only orchestrates and inspects). Reports: events after
+     a terminal run event; node lifecycle for undeclared nodes;
+     `attempt_completed` without a matching `attempt_started`; replayed
+     `total_cost_usd` diverging from the sum of per-node `cost_usd`.
+  3. *Filesystem cross-check* — node directories on disk under the run dir that
+     no journal event mentions (orphans); directories the journal declares that
+     are missing on disk; a `runs/.lock` referencing this run whose recorded
+     process is dead (stale lock, WARNING).
+
+  `--repair` applies ONLY safe mechanical fixes, each reported: drop a torn
+  final journal line (back up to `journal.jsonl.bak`, then write-tmp + atomic
+  rename); remove a stale `runs/.lock` for this run. It REFUSES (clear error,
+  nothing modified) when the run is active (lock held by a live process) or the
+  journal has errors beyond the torn final line. `--json` emits a
+  machine-readable findings list (severity, code, message, evidence path).
+- **Motivation:** Crashes, manual tampering, and engine bugs can leave a
+  journal or run directory degraded. Operators need a diagnosis-plus-safe-repair
+  tool that never guesses at semantic repairs and reuses the single replay
+  source of truth.
+- **Acceptance criteria:**
+  - **Tests:** `run-doctor_test.ts`, `cli_test.ts` (FR-E83; regression-locked;
+    clean run exit 0; torn last line WARNING exit 0; mid-file garbage ERROR
+    exit 1; unknown kind; events after terminal; cost-sum divergence; orphan
+    node dir; missing declared dir; stale lock; `--repair` torn-line round-trip
+    with `.bak` byte-identical except the torn tail; `--repair` refusal on a
+    live lock and on mid-file garbage; `--json` shape; arg parsing).
+
