+# `runs doctor` — journal health checker with mechanical repair
+
+## Goal
+
+Add a `runs doctor` CLI subcommand that diagnoses a run's durability
+artifacts (`journal.jsonl`, node directories, `runs/.lock`) and can apply
+ONLY safe mechanical repairs (drop a torn final journal line; remove a
+stale lock). Diagnosis reuses the EXISTING replayer as the single source
+of replay truth — doctor orchestrates and inspects, never re-implements
+replay.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+- A run's only durable record is its append-only `journal.jsonl`, replayed
+  by `src/state/run-journal.ts::replayRunJournal` to reconstruct `RunState`.
+- The writer already tolerates a torn FINAL line (crash artifact) — it
+  truncates the partial tail on `RunJournalWriter.open`. Doctor must mirror
+  that tolerance (torn tail = WARNING, not ERROR).
+- Path/lock knowledge already lives in helpers: `getJournalPath`,
+  `getRunDir` (`src/state/state.ts`), `defaultLockPath` + `readLockInfo`
+  (`src/state/lock.ts`). Doctor MUST reuse them — no duplicated path or
+  lock-parse logic.
+
+### Current State
+
+- No `runs` subcommand exists. `src/cli.ts` dispatches `run`/`answer`/
+  `init`/`mcp` via a manual `switch`/`if` arg loop.
+- `replayRunJournal` throws on mid-file malformed lines, missing
+  `run_started`, and mixed run-ids; ignores unknown `kind` (switch has no
+  default); dedupes by `event_id`; recomputes `total_cost_usd` from node
+  snapshots via `updateRunCost`.
+- `lock.ts` has internal `isProcessAlive` (not exported) and exported
+  `defaultLockPath`/`readLockInfo`/`isRunLive`.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Follow the existing manual arg-parsing style in `src/cli.ts`; NO new deps.
+- The existing replayer is the single source of replay truth; do NOT write
+  a second replayer. Doctor's journal-integrity scan is a LINE-level lint
+  (parse each line, no state reconstruction) — not a replayer.
+- Reuse `src/state/` helpers for run/node/lock paths and lock parsing.
+- `deno task check` stays green (fmt/lint/type/doc-lint/publish-dry-run/
+  FR-field-set/comment-scan). Register FR-E83 in
+  `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md`, add the index/
+  back-pointer rows.
+- Error handling: doctor never throws on a degraded run — every problem is
+  a reported finding. Replay exceptions are caught and surfaced as ERROR
+  findings, not propagated.
+
+## Solution
+
+### Variant (selected: B — Architecturally-correct, dedicated module)
+
+- **A. Quick fix** — inline all doctor logic in `cli.ts`. Cons: bloats the
+  718-line CLI, untestable without spawning the process, mixes IO orchestration
+  with arg parsing. Rejected.
+- **B. Dedicated `src/state/run-doctor.ts` module (SELECTED)** — a pure-ish
+  `diagnoseRun()` returning a structured `DoctorReport`, plus `repairRun()`;
+  `cli.ts` only parses args + prints. Pros: unit-testable on fabricated run
+  dirs (matches the required test matrix), keeps CLI thin, lives beside the
+  artifacts it inspects (`src/state/`). Cons: one new file. **Best for** the
+  durability/recovery area where the replayer and lock helpers already live.
+- **C. Best long-term** — a generic pluggable "run check registry". Over-
+  engineered for one subcommand with a fixed check list; deferred.
+
+Rationale for autonomous selection: the required test matrix (clean/torn/
+garbage/unknown-kind/after-terminal/cost-divergence/orphan/missing/stale-lock/
+repair round-trip/refusals/json shape) demands the logic be callable without
+the process boundary — only B delivers that while honoring the "reuse helpers,
+single replayer" constraints.
+
+### Files
+
+- **NEW `src/state/run-doctor.ts`**: types + `diagnoseRun()` + `repairRun()`.
+  - `Severity = "error" | "warning"`.
+  - `DoctorFinding { severity, code, message, evidence? }`.
+  - `DoctorReport { findings, hasError }`.
+  - `RepairOutcome { applied: RepairAction[], refused?: string }`.
+  - `diagnoseRun({ workflowDir, runId }): Promise<DoctorReport>`:
+    - **(a) journal integrity** — own line scan of `getJournalPath(runDir)`:
+      missing file → ERROR; unparsable non-final → ERROR; unparsable final +
+      no trailing newline → WARNING (torn tail, record byte offset); unknown
+      `kind` (not in `KNOWN_KINDS`) → ERROR; duplicate `event_id` → WARNING;
+      `seq` strictly decreasing (non-dup) → ERROR.
+    - **(b) replay invariants** — `try { replayRunJournal(runDir) }`; on throw
+      add ERROR `replay.failed` (only if no parse-level ERROR already explains
+      it). On success inspect `result.events` (deduped, ordered):
+      event after a terminal kind → ERROR; node lifecycle for an undeclared
+      node → ERROR; `attempt_completed` w/o prior `attempt_started` (same node)
+      → ERROR; per-node attempt-cost vs replayed node cost reconciliation →
+      ERROR `replay.cost_divergence` (compare, over nodes that HAVE attempt
+      cost events, Σ node.cost_usd vs Σ last-attempt cost_usd; avoids false
+      positives on attempt-less/merge nodes and multi-attempt nodes since
+      `markNodeCompleted` records the completing attempt's cost).
+    - **(c) filesystem** — declared dirs from `node_directory_declared` events
+      resolved under `runDir` (path tail after `runs/<runId>/`): missing on
+      disk → ERROR `fs.declared_dir_missing`. Orphans: immediate children of
+      `runDir` (minus reserved `logs`/`worktree`/`.hitl-inbox`, files) whose
+      basename ∉ mentioned node-ids → ERROR `fs.orphan_dir`; one-level phase
+      grouping handled (a non-node child holding known node-id grandchildren is
+      treated as a phase dir, grandchildren checked instead). Stale lock:
+      `defaultLockPath(workflowDir)` → `readLockInfo`; names this `runId` and
+      pid not alive → WARNING `fs.stale_lock`.
+  - `repairRun({ workflowDir, runId, report }): Promise<RepairOutcome>`:
+    - Refuse (nothing modified) if the run is active (lock names this runId +
+      live pid), OR any journal/replay ERROR exists (beyond the torn tail).
+    - Else: torn tail present → back up to `journal.jsonl.bak`, write
+      `journal.jsonl.tmp` with bytes `[0, validByteLength)`, atomic
+      `Deno.rename` over the original. Stale lock present → `Deno.remove`.
+- **MODIFY `src/state/lock.ts`**: export `isLockHeldByLiveProcess(info)` =
+  `isProcessAlive(info.pid)` so doctor reuses the alive check (no duplication).
+- **MODIFY `src/cli.ts`**: `parseRunsDoctorArgs(args)` (exported, manual loop:
+  `--workflow`, `--run`, `--repair`, `--json`), `runRunsDoctor(args)` (prints
+  grouped report or JSON, exit 0 iff no ERROR / refusal → 1). Dispatch
+  `runs doctor`; add to `printUsage`.
+
+### Error handling strategy
+
+- `diagnoseRun` catches `replayRunJournal` throws and converts to findings —
+  never propagates, so a corrupt journal still yields exit 1 + a report, not a
+  stack trace.
+- `repairRun` is fail-safe: all-or-nothing refusals print a clear reason and
+  modify nothing; the journal rewrite is write-tmp-then-rename (atomic), bak
+  taken before any mutation.
+
+### Verification
+
+- `deno task check` (full gate).
+- New `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts` (FR-E83 marker) covering the full
+  required matrix on fabricated run dirs.
+- `src/cli_test.ts` cases for `parseRunsDoctorArgs`.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts`, `deno task check`) `runs doctor`
+  diagnoses journal integrity, replay invariants, and filesystem cross-check;
+  reports every problem grouped by severity; exit 0 iff no ERROR.
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::*repair*`, `deno task check`)
+  `--repair` drops a torn final line (bak preserved, byte-identical except the
+  torn tail) and removes a stale lock; refuses on a live lock or journal errors
+  beyond the torn tail.
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/state/run-doctor_test.ts::*json*`, `deno task check`)
+  `--json` emits a findings list (severity, code, message, evidence).
+- [x] (FR-E83, `src/cli_test.ts`, `deno task check`) subcommand parses
+  `--workflow`/`--run`/`--repair`/`--json` and appears in `--help`.
+- [x] (FR-E83, manual — korchasa) FR-E83 section added to
+  `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md` with `**Acceptance:**`,
+  plus index + SRS back-pointer rows.
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- Generic pluggable check registry (variant C) if more `runs` health checks
+  are added later.
+- Multi-run batch mode and journal compaction are explicitly out of scope.
+</content>
+</invoke>
